Quintessence Gaming Guild<BR>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uupyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Upyer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0> at: 5/15/01 2:14:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubethude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bethude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 12:40:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Absor may be acting like a smart ass here, but he's right.  If enough wizards run around saying how bad they suck, people will start to believe it.  I hear people say paladins suck but I've seen some that are very well played and certainly earn their right in the group.  Unfortunately, a lot of people will just think all pally's are useless because their damage output isn't very good.  <br>
<br>
A lot of the problem stems from the fixation on DPS.  Everyone's convinced that DPS is the only thing that matters.  The reality is that DPS is important but it's far from the only thing that's important.  Good players know this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uragbert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragbert</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://apollo.lpg.fi/~jsalo/smr10.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 12:55:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.lpg.fi/~jsalo/ragicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> DPS... Yes, I don't think wizard put those melee gear upgrades to the game though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uupyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Upyer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 1:30:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.klm.utvinternet.com/kevins.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> Oh I know it too - but it goes a long way to the bottom line. We have to have more usefulness in a group that is in fitting with our class.<br>
<br>
More damage in certain ways seems like the answer. There's no point starting to redefine what a wizard is and making us Masters of Arcane Teleportation or some such.<br>
<br>
I can see why they are stuck. Bane spels or mob specific spells are NOT the way forward though. I don't play the game to wait 60 levels (God what play time must that be??) to get two spells for a handful of dragons that supposedly defines the class. It don;t add up.<br>
<br>
Here's an idea. Some spells from D&amp;D like:<br>
<br>
Web (area effect movement disabler - creatures get caught in a web). Effects the actual area unline BoF which hits on the creatures who then move with it.<br>
<br>
Cloudkill (a cloud of deadly gas that, again, effect an area)<br>
<br>
Group Invis 15' radius.<br>
<br>
etc etc - just go look at the D&amp;D manuals. If these guys actually wanted to fix us they woulda done this already though I suspect.<br>
 <p>Uproar Solarwind aka
Kevin McCaughey<BR>
Founder<BR>
Quintessence Gaming Guild<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yiliamar>Yiliamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 2:01:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> Perception... It happened to the rangers.  It's happened to us.  We change our perception of ourselves, then change them with others.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uragbert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragbert</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://apollo.lpg.fi/~jsalo/smr10.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 2:07:11 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://apollo.lpg.fi/~jsalo/ragicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> Teleports will never get us a seat in that group. For any group member to be added to the group, he has to bring in something. Group needs damage output (melee, nukes), damage absorption (tanking, healing) and as few utilities as necessary (there is a point in which that summon bread just does not add anything).<br>
<br>
I hope they are going to do something on indirect damage output since direct damage is out of the question. The only other way for us is indirect damage absorption (rune and other shields) and utilities. Utilities is bad for us since they are hardly essential - you can still do without sow, summons, ultravision etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uupyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Upyer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 2:07:41 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.klm.utvinternet.com/kevins.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> I'm not going to rise to it Yil <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
