(21, Dwarf, Rogue)
<BR>
Rukus (6, Half-elven, Bongo Banging Bard)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uupyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Upyer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 6:22:14 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.klm.utvinternet.com/kevins.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> Well I don't think we're all bad. In fact pre Kunark we were well worth playing and just as viable as other classes.<br>
<br>
The whole game is now unbalanced though. The scaled up damage output from tanks due to scaled up weapons led to scaled up mobs. Casters didn't get damage output spells scaled up though and that means Wizards, who are dependant more than all others on their damage outpu, consequently lost out more than all others. <br>
<br>
A reason that this scaled up out of proportion mellee damage did not lead to large scale exploitation and too much unbalancing in the &quot;old world&quot; is that there aren;t these Uber items in the old world and not the same amount of high level dungeons for them to fight in. What if our damage spell rampup was in spells above 50?. Put a level cap on some items also to stop *some* high level items going into ickle level 5 characters in the old world and unbalancing it.<br>
<br>
I think they screwed it by putting too many uber items and mobs with Uber HP in. They should ahve managed the expansion from 50-60 a LOT better.<br>
<br>
Now we have a mess that can't be worked out without either a sop to Wizards, a slap in the face to Wizards, or even more imbalance possibly. I dunno - I keep changing my mind about this. Just wish Verant would be brave and put everything on the table and see what can be done rather than just fighting a rearguard action against ANY change.<br>
<br>
I still maintain though that the change in the 50-60 level game inpacted us more than any other class and it was FAR from a positive impact. WE DO HAVE ISSUES - we're not just whiners!!<br>
