<br>
I play a wizard, I like wizards, but anytime I put together a group, I'm sad to say, I don't let other wizards in. I usually go for a warrior, healer, chanter, and try to fill the other 2 spots with a rogue/monk/ranger or warrior.  I won't even invite any other casters to fill the open spots, not because people say they suck, but because my experience is that you can kill more mobs faster with an additional meleeer.  As far as paladins and sks go, I get any other meleeer first.  Why? because they do more damage, regardless of how well played the paladin or sk is, it's not based on paladins/sks whining, it's based on seeing them in action.<br>
Heck, I didn't even know they did whine, and I surely don't read their message boards.<br>
<br>
I play my wizard, I see how in a steady group I generally cast 1-2 stuns and a single nuke per pull (if that, and that's with clarity).  I know I'm an xp mooch.  Would I want another one in the group?  Heck no!  I have a limited amount of time to play, while I'm playing I wanna maximize my xp return, and that doesn't involve adding more wizards.<br>
<br>
I know someone is gonna say, well you already have a wizard, you don't need more than one.  We're not a specialty class, we don't mez, we don't buff, we don't heal.  We don't have a specialty ability that is required, but not duplicatable (aside from the rare cases where you need evac, but why not get a healer/buffer/evaccer in that case).  We do damage, that's is, therefore we're interchangeable with any other damage dealer for the 3 or so damage dealer spots.  If wizards could hold their weight, they'd be in the runnings to fill the damage dealer slots, reality, we're last on the list of damage dealing classes to fill those spots.  Why get a wizard for this slot when you can get a meleer who can do substantially more damage over the course of the grouping sessions and take a little bit of damage if need be.<br>
<br>
It's not perception people, it's reality.  However much we whine, it's not gonna change the days of firsthand experience seeing what classes/groups are good that everyone 45+ has had.  I don't need to see a bunch of parsed logs comparing damage to tell me how much I sit on my ass and how little I contribute in an xp group, I get to experience it firsthand. <p><hr>
<font size=+1><b>
Igronimus von Gnomus
</b></font><br>
<i>52nd Level Wizard</i><br>
<i>Clan Impact - Innoruuk</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 7:05:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> Bethude, it's not a perception problem, and Wizards didn't invent it. That's assinine. No one wants Wizards.. how many times do I see &quot;fast xp group lfm&quot; and I apply, and hear, &quot;we need a healer&quot;, or &quot;we really need another tank&quot;.<br>
<br>
At any level you can look at the Wizard and look at any other caster class than cleric, and NOT ONLY does our dmg/hour pale, but most of them have comparable nukes. Yes, they can't cast them as rapidly in succession as we can.. BUT NEITHER CAN WE. WE get killed if we try. Sure, if the shit hits the fan, we can try to mix root nuke concussion as fast as we can, but xp groups avoid those situations, and an enchanter can handle those situations with one application of mesmerization, wheras if we do we are completely oom. And every other caster class offers something else besides damage/hour than we do. We have the LOWEST damage per hour. And we offer nothing else.<br>
<br>
I NEVER say how much I suck in a group, hell I play the court jester, give up loots, anything to prove what a swell person I am so I'll get a group next time. But everyone knows the facts.<br>
<br>
We are complaining because we DON'T get groups. If we did we wouldn't complain. Most Wizards past 40, probably are a little masochistic and enjoy the challenge of being arguably the hardest class to play. If we could just get by. If we were just on par.<br>
<br>
Cleetus, I hate to use ad hominem logic, but you just need to pipe down in the peanut gallery until you have a clue.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalagis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malagis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 7:14:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all our own fault</span><hr size=1> Yah,<br>
I started doin Seb at 50 (had my key at 46). But its frustrating as all get out. Blue Krup wizards (i'm 53 now) have so many HPs that I can burn a full tank of mana on one mob and do about 50% of its life. So we're, or at least I'm, really not all that much help in an overpull situation anymore.<br>
<br>
I used to pride myself on my timing. Back in SolB and CoM in my 40s I could get to the point with a group that I would take every mob instantly from berserk to run/death (in CoM they generally dont run, so the goal was next melee shot after spell lands is death blow) and remain at 70-80 mana with constant pulls. This is no longer an option, when one spell does 1/20 of a mobs total health theres a lot of berserk time that I cant do anything about. Stuns are ok, but not particularly mana-efficient. Lately I've been using Tears quite a bit, as it can really increase the mana efficiency, and doesnt aggro nearly as much. The only downside is resist rate.<br>
